      "playtime_at_review": 1097,
      "review_text": "Simple, fun, addictive.\r\n\r\nIt's a 1990s VHS video rental store simulator. For those of you who have ever worked a menial service job, the experience will feel very familiar. The job sounds easy, and it certainly [i]can[/i] be, but it can get surprisingly tricky to balance stocking inventory, choralling your employees, and keeping your customers happy enough that they don't throw a rainbow slushy at you during busy days.\r\n\r\nThere's a lot of love woven into this game. I'm reminded of the original \"The SIms\", where there's a lot of really fun and weird stuff just waiting for you find it if you go looking for it. I can tell that the dev had a very strong cultural sense of 90s and early 00s aesthetics, and that nostalgia is perfectly encapsulated in this simulator.",
      "timestamp_created": 1774131950
    },
